<p><strong>Novel Photon Storage</strong><br />
 February 9, 2013<br />
 Rydberg polaritons offer a new way to hold and manipulate photons.<br />
 <img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> Article: <em><a href="http://physicsworld.com/cws/article/news/2013/feb/05/stored-photons-interact-in-atom-cloud">Physics World</a></em><br />
 <img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> Abstract: <em><a href="http://prl.aps.org/accepted/63070Y36K4c1e120f9ea4496fc7813d2584864952">Phys Rev Letters</a></em></p>

<p><strong>Persistent Nanobubbles</strong><br />
 February 4, 2013<br />
 Why do tiny bubbles survive longer than expected on surfaces?<br />
 <img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> Article: <em><a href="http://phys.org/news/2013-02-physics-duo-explanation-tiny-longer.html">PhysOrg</a></em><br />
 <img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> Synopsis: <em><a href="http://physics.aps.org/synopsis-for/10.1103/PhysRevLett.110.054501">Physics</a></em></p>

<p><strong>Moniz May Replace Chu</strong><br />
 February 11, 2013<br />
 MIT's Ernest Moniz is rumored to be likely candidate for Energy Secretary appointment.<br />
 <img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> Article: <em><a href="http://www.pressandguide.com/articles/2013/02/09/news/doc5116c19a95405702566875.txt?viewmode=2">Press and Guide</a></em></p>

<p><strong>Lifelike Crystals</strong><br />
 February 1, 2013<br />
 Collections of colloidal particles exhibit many lifelike characteristics.<br />
 <img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> Article: <em><a href="http://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2013-02/01/living-crystals">Wired</a></em></p>

<p><strong>Football Helmet Physics</strong><br />
 February 1, 2013<br />
