<a name="textblocknohdr27109" id="textblocknohdr27109"></a><a name="CP_JUMP_27109" id="CP_JUMP_27109"></a><div id="cs_control_27109" class="cs_control CS_Element_Textblock"><div class="CS_Textblock_Text"><h3>President Obama Touts R&amp;D Support in State of the Union Address</h3>

<p>President Obama exhorted that, "Now is the time to reach a level of research and development not seen since the height of the Space Race." He added that automatic spending cuts scheduled to take effect March 1 would devastate American priorities, including research. The President supports a balanced approach to achieving deficit reduction as outlined in the Simpson-Bowles Commission.<br />
<img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" /> <a class="CP___PAGEID_273243" href="/about/pressreleases/sotu2013.cfm">Read APS Press Release</a></p>

<h3>Outstanding Journal Referees</h3>

<p><strong>142 Referees Honored</strong><br />
<a id="http://publish.aps.org/OutstandingReferees" onmouseover="return window.status='http://publish.aps.org/OutstandingReferees'" href="http://publish.aps.org/OutstandingReferees"><img title="Outstanding Referees lapel pin" style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 0.3em 0.4em;" alt="Outstanding Referees lapel pin" src="/images/referees.gif" border="0" width="90" height="95" hspace="0" /></a>APS currently has over 60,000 active referees.  The  Outstanding Referees Program recognizes scientists who have been exceptionally helpful in assessing journals manuscripts.  The 2013 honorees come from 49 different countries, with large contingents from the U.S., Germany, Canada, Spain, Great Britain, and France.<br />
<img alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" />  <a href="http://publish.aps.org/OutstandingReferees">2013 Outstanding Referees</a></p>

<h3>Nominating APS Officers</h3>

<p>The APS Nominating Committee requests your nominations for the 2013 APS Leadership Elections.<br />
