<h3>Graduate Education in Physics Conference</h3>

<p>Sponsored by APS and the American Association of Physics Teachers (AAPT), the Graduate Education in Physics Conference was attended by over 100 physicists and grad students from 74 institutions.<br />
<img title="Gray arrow" alt="Gray arrow" src="/policy/issues/research-funding/images/gray_arrow_3.gif" border="0" width="6" height="7" hspace="0" />  <a href="/programs/education/graduate/conf2013/index.cfm">Graduate Education in Physics Conference Program and Resources</a></p>

<p style="text-align:center; font-size:.9em"><a href="/programs/education/graduate/conf2013/index.cfm" style="cursor:hand" id="/programs/education/graduate/conf2013/index.cfm"><img src="/programs/education/graduate/conf2013/images/snidertalk.jpg" alt="Stefan Zollner speaking" title="Stefan Zollner speaking" border="0" vspace="0" width="415" height="219" hspace="0" /></a><br />
During a breakout session, Stefan Zollner (standing) of New Mexico State described non-academic career options for physicists.</p></div></div>
